{"insight":"Do not let silence name you","publicTitle":"When Silence Is Not Your Judge","plainSummary":"After practice, quiet is a place to return from, not a verdict on who you are.","atAGlance":"After practice, a blank or quiet mind can feel like a final answer. It is not one. Do one small act of care before naming what happened. Let your life, your trusted people, and your next choices test the meaning.","keyPoints":["Quiet can deepen practice without deciding your worth.","Lonely or driven people risk turning calm into another self-test.","Watch whether care and honesty grow after the experience."],"match":["stop making silence judge you"],"tags":["practice","care","worth","attention"]}
